# Aman IoT — Environment Configuration
#
# 1. Create a Telegram bot via @BotFather on Telegram
#    - Send /newbot and follow the prompts
#    - Copy the bot token below
#
# 2. Choose your LLM provider and add the API key
#
# 3. Connect your IoT devices to send data to this same bot:
#    - Your ESP32, Raspberry Pi, or Arduino sends HTTP requests
#      to the Telegram Bot API using this same bot token
#    - Both your device messages AND your own Telegram messages
#      go to the same bot — Aman IoT handles both
#    - Device messages format: "sensor:my-sensor-01 temp:28.5 humidity:75"
#    - See content/guides/getting-started.md for device code examples

# Telegram Bot Token (required)
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here

# LLM Provider — pick ONE:
# Option A: Anthropic (recommended)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_key_here

# Option B: OpenAI
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here

# Option C: Ollama (free, local — no key needed)
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3
